         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility"> ¶ This is a form of A. polybotrya which came up amongst seed collected by me many years ago on or near Seaview Range and 60 miles from Cardwell ¶  the tree never seeded at Bowen Park &amp; is [...] ¶ FMB...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">87.00.00d</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">From Frederick Bailey</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">MEL 2078486, National Herbarium of Victoria, Royal Botanic Gardens Melbourne.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Note found with specimen of <seg style="font-style: italic; ">Acacia baileyana</seg>. The note is dated on the basis of its evident connection with the items cited in n. 3.</p>
               </note>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>This is a form of A. polybotrya which came up amongst seed collected by me many years ago on or near Seaview Range and 60 miles from Cardwell<note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Qld.</p>
               </note> the tree never seeded at Bowen Park &amp; is [...]</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">FMB<note xml:id="ftn3" type="footnote" n="3">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>After initially accepting Bailey's identification of the species, M had second thoughts and decided it was a new species that he described in B88.07.03 as <seg style="font-style: italic; ">A, baileyana</seg>; see M to Bailey, 22 November 1887 and M to W. Thiselton-Dyer, 9 April 1888. The specimen sheet includes M's herbarium label: 'Acacia Baileyana F.v.M. | Cultiv. In Bowen's Park Brisbane. | F. M. Bailey'.</p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
